    • Method Detail

      • ifPresent

        public static <T,E extends Throwable> Premise ifPresent(Optional<T> optional,
                                                        CheckedConsumer<? super T,E> consumer)
                                                 throws E extends Throwable
        Invokes consumer if optional is present. Returns a Premise object to allow orElse() and friends to be chained. For example: 
           ifPresent(findStory(), Story::tell)
       .orElse(() -> print("no story"));

        This method is very similar to JDK Optional.ifPresent(java.util.function.Consumer<? super T>) with a few differences:

        1. orElse() is chained fluently, compared to Optional#ifPresentOrElse.
        2. Propagates checked exceptions from the consumer.
        3. Syntax is consistent across one-Optional and two-Optional ifPresent() overloads.
        4. ifPresent(findStory(), Story::tell) begins the statement with "if", which may read somewhat closer to regular if statements.
        Throws:
        E extends Throwable

        Invokes consumer if both left and right are present. Returns a Premise object to allow orElse() and friends to be chained. For example: 
           ifPresent(when, where, Story::tell)
       .orElse(() -> print("no story"));
